The paper discusses a method for training stochastic attention networks for image classification and caption generation. This involves techniques from the literature on training deep generative models, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of attention models also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL), while the mention of stochastic gradient estimates suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
